<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="67" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="67">Description of male.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="67">Length including wings in repose 3.9 mm, maximum width 1.8 mm. Pronotum, wings, and leg features as described for genus. Pronotum black with small white spot along the lateral margin and white V-shaped band before apex (Fig. 6). Male genitalia (Fig. 11). Pygofer with lateral plate separated; subgenital plates fused basally to about mid length; styles hooked distally, recurved anterolaterally; aedaeagus U-shaped, shaft weakly expanded, flat anteriorly, margins and surface without dentae or serrations, gonopore posterior.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="67">Female unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
